<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D23208FFF05CCF0439FBE9FA98" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D19AB593208FFF05CCF0439FD9EFB58" blockId="6.[166,1225,1087,1370]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. From Fennoscandia southwards to Iberian Peninsula and round the Mediterranean to 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF05D6E0426FE3AFBBB" box="[378,462,1119,1145]" name="Greece" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF05DCC0426FDD9FBBB" box="[472,557,1119,1145]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and N Africa; from 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF05F0D0426FC9AFBBB" box="[793,878,1119,1145]" name="Ireland" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Ireland</collectingCountry>
eastwards through Eurasia to the Pacific coast; 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF05D6404F9FE56FB58" box="[368,418,1152,1178]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E937D6A83208FFF05DA40406FDA9FB58" author="Gilasian, E." box="[432,605,1151,1178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" pagination="75 - 76" refId="ref6509" refString="Gilasian, E. New record of one genus and six species of Syrphidae (Diptera) from Iran // J. Entomological Society of Iran. - 2005. - 25, N 1. - P. 75 - 76." type="book chapter" year="2005">Gilasian, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB593208FFF05CCF04D9FBE9FA98" blockId="6.[166,1225,1087,1370]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Eye bare; antennal sockets non-separated, anterior process of lunule not fused with dorsal part of face, third segment of antenna brownishblack (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05CE304A6FEC2FB3B" box="[247,310,1247,1273]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF05D5204A6FEA1FB3B" box="[326,341,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">h</emphasis>
); face without hairs (microtrichia not taken into account); median facial tubercle wide, occupying face from margin to margin in dorsal view; at least mid tibia in basal 1/3 and first segment of mid tarsus yellow dorsally, or 2nd–4th segments of fore and mid tarsi distinctly paler than others (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05E740546FD68FA9B" box="[608,668,1343,1369]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF05EBD0539FD41FA9B" box="[681,693,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">g</emphasis>
); male genitalia as in (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05FA80546FC0CFA9B" box="[956,1016,1343,1369]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF058100539FBF8FA9B" box="[1028,1036,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">i</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
